{"metadata":{"kernelspec":{"language":"python","display_name":"Python 3","name":"python3"},"language_info":{"name":"python","version":"3.12.13","mimetype":"text/x-python","codemirror_mode":{"name":"ipython","version":3},"pygments_lexer":"ipython3","nbconvert_exporter":"python","file_extension":".py"},"kaggle":{"accelerator":"none","dataSources":[],"dockerImageVersionId":28755,"isInternetEnabled":false,"language":"python","sourceType":"notebook","isGpuEnabled":false}},"nbformat_minor":4,"nbformat":4,"cells":[{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"# 🗺️ The Complete Kaggle Roadmap\nWe will build this model through 3 dedicated notebooks to keep our memory allocations clean. Here is how our architecture maps out:\n\n* Notebook 1 (CPU Runtime): Data Engineering — Read the Kaggle Bible JSON dataset, process it, and output the 3 custom .jsonl configurations.\n\n* Notebook 2 (GPU T4 Runtime): Training Loops — Execute Continual Pre-training, Supervised Fine-Tuning (SFT), and Preference Alignment (DPO), saving our separate parameter weights as clean adapters.\n\n* Notebook 3 (High-RAM CPU Runtime): The Fuser — Load the base model, stack our adapters, execute a full 16-bit float weight merge, and push it directly to the Kaggle Model Registry.\n\n# 🛠️ Phase 1: Data Engineering (Notebook 1)\n## Step 1: Initialize the Environment\n* Go to Kaggle and click the \"+\" Create button in the top left corner, then select New Notebook.\n\n* Look at the right-hand panel named Data. Click on \"+ Add Input\".\n\n* In the search bar, paste: rajeshkumarkarra/cleaned-kjv-bible-for-llms and click \"Add\".\n\n* Keep the default notebook accelerator set to CPU (do not waste GPU hours on data formatting).","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"# Step 1: Run the Kaggle Data Parser\nCreate a code cell and paste this script. It dynamically scans Kaggle's /input directory, processes the nested hierarchical JSON format, and saves the 3 target training text files into your notebook's writeable output sandbox:","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"import json\nimport os\nimport random\n\ninput_root = \"/kaggle/input\"\ninput_json_path = None\n\n# 1. Target 'kjv_bible_dataset.json' path dynamically\nfor root, dirs, files in os.walk(input_root):\n    for filename in files:\n        if filename == \"kjv_bible_dataset.json\":\n            input_json_path = os.path.join(root, filename)\n            print(f\"🎯 Target Found -> {input_json_path}\")\n            break\n    if input_json_path:\n        break\n\nif not input_json_path:\n    raise FileNotFoundError(\"❌ Could not find 'kjv_bible_dataset.json'. Ensure the dataset input is attached.\")\n\n# Archaic substitution dictionary for preference mapping (DPO)\narchaic_to_modern_slang = {\n    \"God\": \"the universe\", \"LORD\": \"the big boss\", \"heaven\": \"sky\", \"earth\": \"dirt\",\n    \"shepherd\": \"manager\", \"shall not want\": \"am totally fine\", \"created\": \"spawned\",\n    \"unto\": \"to\", \"thee\": \"you\", \"thou\": \"you\", \"thy\": \"your\", \"shalt\": \"will\"\n}\n\ndef generate_rejected_text(text):\n    words = text.split()\n    modified_words = [archaic_to_modern_slang.get(w.strip(\".,;:?!\"), w) for w in words]\n    return \" \".join(modified_words) + \" i guess, idk lol.\"\n\nraw_dataset = []\ninstruction_dataset = []\npreference_dataset = []\n\n# 2. Open and deserialize the dataset\nwith open(input_json_path, 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f:\n    bible_data = json.load(f)\n\n# If it's wrapped in an outer dictionary node, unbox it to get the list\nif isinstance(bible_data, dict):\n    for key, val in bible_data.items():\n        if isinstance(val, list):\n            bible_data = val\n            break\n\nprint(f\"Traversing {len(bible_data)} top-level structural elements...\")\n\n# 3. Deep Extraction Recursive Loop\nfor entry_idx, entry in enumerate(bible_data):\n    if not isinstance(entry, dict):\n        continue\n    \n    # Check if this object holds a nested list of elements/verses\n    nested_list = None\n    for k, v in entry.items():\n        if isinstance(v, list):\n            nested_list = v\n            break\n            \n    # Context extraction fallback references\n    parent_book = entry.get(\"book\") or entry.get(\"Book\") or \"Scripture\"\n    parent_chapter = entry.get(\"chapter\") or entry.get(\"Chapter\") or \"1\"\n\n    # Scenario A: The object contains an internal collection array\n    if nested_list is not None:\n        for inner_idx, item in enumerate(nested_list):\n            if isinstance(item, dict):\n                clean_text = str(item.get(\"text\") or item.get(\"Text\") or item.get(\"verse\") or \"\").strip()\n                book_name = str(item.get(\"book\") or item.get(\"Book\") or parent_book).strip()\n                chapter_num = str(item.get(\"chapter\") or item.get(\"Chapter\") or parent_chapter).strip()\n                verse_num = str(item.get(\"verse\") or item.get(\"Verse\") or f\"{inner_idx+1}\").strip()\n            else:\n                clean_text = str(item).strip()\n                book_name = parent_book\n                chapter_num = parent_chapter\n                verse_num = f\"{inner_idx+1}\"\n                \n            if not clean_text or len(clean_text) < 3:\n                continue\n                \n            reference = f\"{book_name} {chapter_num}:{verse_num}\"\n            \n            raw_dataset.append({\"text\": f\"{reference} - {clean_text}\"})\n            \n            instruction_templates = [\n                f\"Provide the scripture for {reference}.\",\n                f\"What is written in the book of {book_name}, chapter {chapter_num}, verse {verse_num}?\",\n                f\"Quote {reference} from the King James Bible.\"\n            ]\n            instruction_dataset.append({\"instruction\": random.choice(instruction_templates), \"input\": \"\", \"output\": clean_text})\n            preference_dataset.append({\"instruction\": f\"Recite {reference} exactly as written in the historical King James Version.\", \"chosen\": clean_text, \"rejected\": generate_rejected_text(clean_text)})\n\n    # Scenario B: The top-level item itself is a single flat verse entry\n    else:\n        clean_text = str(entry.get(\"text\") or entry.get(\"Text\") or \"\").strip()\n        if not clean_text or len(clean_text) < 3:\n            continue\n            \n        book_name = str(entry.get(\"book\") or entry.get(\"Book\") or \"Scripture\").strip()\n        chapter_num = str(entry.get(\"chapter\") or entry.get(\"Chapter\") or \"1\").strip()\n        verse_num = str(entry.get(\"verse\") or entry.get(\"Verse\") or f\"{entry_idx+1}\").strip()\n        \n        reference = f\"{book_name} {chapter_num}:{verse_num}\"\n        \n        raw_dataset.append({\"text\": f\"{reference} - {clean_text}\"})\n        instruction_dataset.append({\"instruction\": f\"Quote {reference} from the King James Bible.\", \"input\": \"\", \"output\": clean_text})\n        preference_dataset.append({\"instruction\": f\"Recite {reference} exactly as written in the historical King James Version.\", \"chosen\": clean_text, \"rejected\": generate_rejected_text(clean_text)})\n\n# 4. Save and verify files on disk\ndef save_local_jsonl(data_list, filename):\n    output_path = os.path.join(\"/kaggle/working\", filename)\n    with open(output_path, 'w', encoding='utf-8', buffering=1) as out_f:\n        for node in data_list:\n            out_f.write(json.dumps(node, ensure_ascii=False) + '\\n')\n        out_f.flush()\n        os.fsync(out_f.fileno())\n    print(f\"Generated -> {filename} | Total Records: {len(data_list):,} | Size: {os.path.getsize(output_path):,} bytes\")\n\nprint(\"\\n--- Saving files to Kaggle workspace ---\")\nsave_local_jsonl(raw_dataset, \"kjv_raw_pretrain.jsonl\")\nsave_local_jsonl(instruction_dataset, \"kjv_instruction_sft.jsonl\")\nsave_local_jsonl(preference_dataset, \"kjv_preference_dpo.jsonl\")\n\nprint(\"\\n🎉 Data Engineering Complete! Check your sizes below.\")","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-06-20T06:24:00.498948Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-06-20T06:24:00.499995Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-06-20T06:24:00.787612Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-06-20T06:24:00.499931Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-06-20T06:24:00.786422Z"}},"outputs":[{"name":"stdout","text":"🎯 Target Found -> /kaggle/input/datasets/rajeshkumarkarra/cleaned-kjv-bible-for-llms/kjv_bible_dataset.json\nTraversing 242 top-level structural elements...\n\n--- Saving files to Kaggle workspace ---\nGenerated -> kjv_raw_pretrain.jsonl | Total Records: 1,234 | Size: 1,675,552 bytes\nGenerated -> kjv_instruction_sft.jsonl | Total Records: 1,234 | Size: 1,758,086 bytes\nGenerated -> kjv_preference_dpo.jsonl | Total Records: 1,234 | Size: 3,481,095 bytes\n\n🎉 Data Engineering Complete! Check your sizes below.\n","output_type":"stream"}],"execution_count":10},{"cell_type":"code","source":"!head -n 2 /kaggle/working/kjv_raw_pretrain.jsonl","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-06-20T06:24:16.105629Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-06-20T06:24:16.105996Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-06-20T06:24:16.347843Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-06-20T06:24:16.105950Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-06-20T06:24:16.346590Z"}},"outputs":[{"name":"stdout","text":"{\"text\": \"Genesis 1:1 - ['In the beginning God created the heaven and the earth.', 'And the earth was without form, and void; and darkness was upon', 'And God said, Let there be light: and there was light.', 'And God saw the light, that it was good: and God divided the light', 'And God called the light Day, and the darkness he called Night.', 'And God said, Let there be a firmament in the midst of the waters,', 'And God made the firmament, and divided the waters which were', 'And God called the firmament Heaven. And the evening and the', 'And God said, Let the waters under the heaven be gathered together', 'And God called the dry land Earth; and